docker/test-emulators/.image-build-hash

# graphify — authoritative, cross-branch tracking policy for graphify-out/.
# TRACKED deliverables (NOT ignored): graph.json, GRAPH_REPORT.md,
# manifest.json, wiki/. Everything below is local/regenerable state that
# `graphify update` rewrites each run — never commit it.
graphify-out/cache/
# graph.html is a ~5 MB deterministic vis.js render of graph.json — no API cost
# and ~0.6 s to rebuild (`graphify export html`), so it is not worth carrying in
# git. Untracking it also sidesteps a graphify bug: `graphify update` passes
# node_limit=None (graphifyy 0.9.5 __main__.py:3679, still present at 0.9.17
# cli.py:1423), so above 5000 nodes to_html raises instead of building the
# documented community-aggregation view and the caller unlink()s graph.html.
# Salt builds ~4995 nodes — a hair under the limit, so adding a few files tips it
# over and silently deletes the file (hit twice while working #518).
graphify-out/graph.html
graphify-out/.graphify_python
graphify-out/.graphify_root
graphify-out/.graphify_labels.json
graphify-out/cost.json
graphify-out/**/.graphify_labels.json
graphify-out/**/cost.json
# Per-run dated snapshot archives (YYYY-MM-DD/) — regenerated, not tracked.
graphify-out/[0-9][0-9][0-9][0-9]-[0-9][0-9]-[0-9][0-9]/
